.TH "getCommand" "1" "" "SequoiaDB User Manuals" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
getCommand \- Get the last executed command.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]\f[I]getCommand()\f[]\f[]
.SH CATEGORY
.PP
Cmd
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Get the last executed command.
.SH PARAMETERS
.PP
NULL
.SH RETURN VALUE
.PP
On success, return the last executed command.
.PP
On error, exception will be thrown.
.SH ERRORS
.PP
when exception happen, use getLastError() to get the error code and use
getLastErrMsg() to get error message.
For more detial, please reference to Troubleshooting.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP \[bu] 2
Create a Command object.
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
>\ var\ cmd\ =\ new\ Cmd()
\f[]
.fi
.IP \[bu] 2
Executed command(For more detial on Command Object executed command, please
reference to Cmd:run).
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
>\ cmd.run(\ "ls",\ "/opt/trunk/test"\ )
test1
test2
test3
\f[]
.fi
.IP \[bu] 2
Get the last executed command.
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
>\ cmd.getCommand()
ls\ /opt/trunk/test
\f[]
.fi
